**Determining the New Administrative Unit for Phường Phúc Thắng**

Okay, so I need to figure out what happened to "Phường Phúc Thắng, Thành phố Phúc Yên, Tỉnh Vĩnh Phúc." The user's provided address is for the old administrative structure. My first step is to check if there have been any changes to "Tỉnh Vĩnh Phúc."  I consulted the document "60-NQ/TW," which lists provincial changes. It clearly states that Vĩnh Phúc merged with Phú Thọ and Hòa Bình to become Phú Thọ.  So, "Tỉnh Vĩnh Phúc" is now part of "Tỉnh Phú Thọ."

Next, I need to find the new ward for "Phường Phúc Thắng" within the new province.  I reviewed the relevant resolutions and found one specifically addressing administrative changes in Phú Thọ: "1676/NQ-UBTVQH15." This is where things get interesting. Line 141 explicitly mentions "Phường Phúc Thắng" and "thành phố Phúc Yên."  It states that "Phường Phúc Thắng" is merged with several other wards to form a new ward called "**phường Phúc Yên**."

Now I must confirm this using the "New wards" data.  I was able to locate a ward with the name "Phường Phúc Yên," which aligns with my finding. This ward has the code "08740" and is indeed located in "Tỉnh Phú Thọ."

I have high confidence in this conclusion since the resolution directly addresses the merger of "Phường Phúc Thắng" into "Phường Phúc Yên."
